Package Manager for sauzerOS
modified kiss by Dylan Araps and Kiss Community
all code written with AI so don't expect good code

Main Changes:
- Expects GNU coreutils, grep, tar, bash
- More environment flags
- Global file for env vars (/etc/kiss/flags)
- Option to set global bin/logs/source dirs
- Option for specific packages to be built in an alternate tmpdir (/etc/kiss/BIG_PKGS)
- Scans all cached sources to avoid duplicate downloads if multiple packages use the same source
- Keeps track of all library deps of a package (/var/db/kiss/installed/pkg/libdeps)
- On update checks if a removed library is used by installed packages and prompts for package rebuilds
- Build time

KISS_INSTALL
1 default   : prompt for install
0 override  : build only

KISS_AUTO
0 default   : prompt for install
1 override  : auto install

KISS_TMPDIR
tmpdir for build

KISS_TMPDIR2
tmpdir for packages set in /etc/kiss/BIG_PKGS
 
KISS_DL
source download tool

KISS_DIRS
kiss dirs path (bin/logs/source)

KISS_QUIET
0 default  : build output to tty
1 override : no build output

KISS_SU
superuser tool for install

KISS_COMPRESSION
package compression

KISS_STRIP
1 default  : strip packages
0 override : disable stripping
can be overriden in build file with :> nostrip

